        <title>SEPA.LIMIT</title>
        <table>SEPA.LIMIT</table>
    </header>
    <overview>
        <ovdesc>
            <p>While processing direct debit collection through Inward Pacs003, checks should be enabled to limit the direct debit transaction on certain conditions. The checks required are</p>
	    <p>1. Limit direct debit collection to a certain amount per transaction</p>	
	    <p>2. Limit direct debit to a certain periodicity</p>
	    <p>3. Limit direct debit to a certain amount AND to a certain periodicity</p>
            <p/>
        </ovdesc>
    </overview>
    <menu>
        <t>
            <field>LIMIT.START.DATE</field>
            <desc>
                <p>This date denotes the starting date for the DD limit check.</p>
                <p/>
                <p>  Validation Rules</p>
                <p>  Value upto 8 type D </p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>LIMIT.FREQUENCY</field>
            <desc>
                <p>This fields contains the frequency for DD limit check to be performed Monthly/Yearly in relation to the number of transaction allowed </p>
                <p/>
                <p/>
                <p>  Validation Rules</p>
                <p>   Value upto 30 type FQU</p>
                <p>   Associated Multi Value SubSet with field LIMIT.START.DATE</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>LIMIT.END.DATE</field>
            <desc>
                <p>This field denotes the end date of the DD limit check. After the end date, the status to the limit record is changed to INACTIVE during COB. </p>
                <p/>
                <p/>
                <p>  Validation Rules</p>
                <p>   Value upto 30 type FQU</p>
                <p>   Associated Multi Value SubSet with field LIMIT.START.DATE</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
            <field>LIMIT.STATUS</field>
            <desc>
                <p>This field denotes the status of the DD limit check record.</p>
                <p/>
                <p/>
                <p>  Validation Rules</p>
                <p>   Allowed Values are ACTIVE, INACTIVE and EXPIRED</p>
                <p>   Associated Multi Value SubSet with field LIMIT.START.DATE</p>
            </desc>
        </t>
        <t>
